1002020.name: Vagrant
1002020.description: In order to survive, some Underworlders are desperate enough to venture deep into the Fragmentum in search of anything salvageable. Ancient machinery that they dug up has become their best helper.

1002030.name: Silvermane Cannoneer
1002030.description: A cannoneer of the Silvermane Guards who wields a portable hand cannon into battle.\nDuring combat, Silvermane Cannoneers will launch brutal chain attacks with their allies.

1002040.name: Silvermane Soldier
1002040.description: A member of Belobog's Silvermane Guards, tasked with leading the charge into enemy lines.\nSilvermane Soldiers' attacks will reduce their enemies' defense during combat.

1002041.name: Silvermane Soldier
1002041.description: A member of Belobog's Silvermane Guards, tasked with leading the charge into enemy lines.\nSilvermane Soldiers' attacks will reduce their enemies' defense during combat.

1002050.name: Silvermane Gunner
1002050.description: A gunner of Belobog's Silvermane Guards, tasked with sniping at enemies.\nSilvermane Gunners' shots will inflict Bleed on their enemies during combat.

1002060.name: Lance of the Eternal Freeze

1002064.name: IPC Team Leader Illusion
1002064.description: An Interastral Peace Corporation senior staff member with a minimal rank of project team leader. The mech they drive belongs to the IPC. If damaged, its repair fees have to be paid out-of-pocket. With a half-decent salary, they can at least afford to rent a one-bedroom apartment on one of the IPC's enterprise ships.

1003010.name: Silvermane Lieutenant
1003010.description: The leader of a squad of Belobog's Silvermane Guards.\nSilvermane Lieutenants can raise a giant shield during combat and Enhance themselves. Attacking a Silvermane Lieutenant with their shield raised will immediately result in a fierce Counter.

1003011.name: Silvermane Lieutenant (Bug)
1003011.description: A false projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is the leader of a squad of Belobog's Silvermane Guards.\nAs long as there are remaining friendly units, Silvermane Lieutenants will persistently raise a giant shield during combat. Attacking a Silvermane Lieutenant with their shield raised will result in a fierce counterattack.

1003012.name: Silvermane Lieutenant (Complete)
1003012.description: A complete projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is the leader of a squad of Belobog's Silvermane Guards.

1003013.name: Silvermane Lieutenant (Complete)
1003013.description: A complete projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is the leader of a squad of Belobog's Silvermane Guards.

1004010.name: Cocolia
1004010.description: The Guardian of Belobog, and the indisputable ruler of the Towering Citadel, Belobog.\nCocolia possesses the divine authority passed down through the generations of Guardians, giving her command over ice and snow to freeze her enemies in battle.

1004011.name: Cocolia (Complete)
1004011.description: A complete projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is the Guardian of Belobog, the indisputable ruler of the Towering Citadel of Belobog.\nAs the Guardian, Cocolia (Complete) has inherited divine powers, giving her absolute command over the power of ice to freeze her enemies in battle.

1004012.name: Cocolia (Complete)
1004012.description: A complete projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is the Guardian of Belobog, the indisputable ruler of the Towering Citadel of Belobog.\nAs the Guardian, Cocolia (Complete) has inherited divine powers, giving her absolute command over the power of ice to freeze her enemies in battle.

1004013.name: Cocolia (Illusion)
1004013.description: The Guardian of Belobog, and the ruler of the Towering Citadel of Belobog.\nAs the Guardian, Cocolia has inherited divine powers, giving her absolute command over the ice to freeze her enemies in battle. This entity is a phantom borne from your memories.

1004014.name: Annihilator of Desolation Mistral
1004014.description: The Annihilator of Desolation Mistral possesses the divine authority passed down through the generations of Guardians, giving her command over ice and snow to freeze her enemies in battle.

1004015.name: Topaz Illusion
1004015.description: An extroverted and socially skilled investment expert, one of the directors of the Strategic Investment Department in the IPC. Leads the Special Debt Marshal Force.

1004017.name: Cocolia (Corrupted)
1004017.description: The Guardian of Belobog, and the indisputable ruler of the Towering Citadel, Belobog.\nCocolia possesses the divine authority passed down through the generations of Guardians, giving her command over ice and snow to freeze her enemies in battle.

1004020.name: Gepard
1004020.description: Captain of the Silvermane Guards.\nGepard can command his soldiers to focus their attacks, and provide each of them with a barrier that blocks one attack.

1004021.name: Gepard
1004021.description: Captain of the Silvermane Guards.\nGepard can command his soldiers to focus their attacks, and provide each of them with a barrier that blocks one attack.

1004022.name: Gepard (Complete)
1004022.description: A complete projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is the leader of the Silvermane Guards.\nGepard (Complete) can command his soldiers to focus their attacks and offer soldiers a shield to block attacks.

1004023.name: Gepard (Complete)
1004023.description: A complete projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is the leader of the Silvermane Guards.\nGepard (Complete) can command his soldiers to focus their attacks and offer soldiers a shield to block attacks.

1004024.name: Gepard (Illusion)
1004024.description: Captain of the Silvermane Guards.\nGepard will provide soldiers with a shield that can block DMG taken. What you see here is a simulated illusion based on your own memories.

1004025.name: Gepard (Illusion)
1004025.description: Leader of the Silvermane Guards.\nGepard can command his soldiers to focus their attacks, and offer a barrier to immune any attack once. This entity is a phantom borne from your memories.

1004026.name: Gepard
1004026.description: Captain of the Silvermane Guards.\nGepard will provide soldiers with a shield that can block DMG taken.

1004027.name: Gepard
1004027.description: Captain of the Silvermane Guards.\nGepard can command his soldiers to focus their attacks, and provide each of them with a barrier that blocks one attack.

1004030.name: Bronya
1004030.description: Successor to Belobog's Guardian, and commander of the Silvermane Guards.\nBronya can use various tactics to attack her enemies, and greatly enhance the battle prowess of all allies.

1004031.name: Bronya (Complete)
1004031.description: A complete projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is Belobog's Guardian successor and commander of the Silvermane Guards.\nBronya (complete) can use various tactics to attack her enemies, and greatly enhance the battle prowess of all allies.

1004032.name: Bronya (Illusion)
1004032.description: Successor to Belobog's Guardian, and commander of the Silvermane Guards.\nBronya can use various tactics to attack her enemies, and greatly enhance the battle prowess of friendly units. This entity is a phantom borne from your memories.

1005010.name: Cocolia, Mother of Deception
1005010.description: After being assimilated by the overflowing Fragmentum energy of the Stellaron, the Supreme Guardian transforms into a singer able to control Imaginary Energy and the mouthpiece of its promised "new world."

1005011.name: Cocolia, Mother of Deception
1005011.description: After being assimilated by the overflowing Fragmentum energy of the Stellaron, the Supreme Guardian transforms into a singer able to control Imaginary Energy and the mouthpiece of its promised "new world."

1005012.name: Cocolia, Mother of Deception
1005012.description: After being assimilated by the overflowing Fragmentum energy of the Stellaron, the Supreme Guardian transforms into a chantress able to control Imaginary Energy and the mouthpiece of the Stellaron's promised "new world."

1005013.name: Cocolia, Mother of Deception (Illusion)
1005013.description: After being assimilated by the overflowing Fragmentum energy of the Stellaron, the Supreme Guardian transforms into a singer able to control Imaginary Energy and the mouthpiece of its promised "new world." This entity is a phantom borne from your memories.

1005014.name: Annihilator of Desolation Mistral: Mother of Deception
1005014.description: After being assimilated by the overflowing Fragmentum energy of the Stellaron, the Supreme Guardian transforms into a chantress able to control Imaginary Energy and the mouthpiece of the Stellaron's promised "new world."

1012010.name: Automaton Hound
1012010.description: An automaton pieced together with Old World technology. It looks like a transportation vehicle whose purpose has long been forgotten.\nIn combat, Automaton Hounds can provide support and restore HP to its allies.

1012011.name: Automaton Hound
1012011.description: An automaton pieced together with Old World technology. It looks like a transportation vehicle whose purpose has long been forgotten.\nIn combat, Automaton Hounds can provide support and restore HP to its allies.

1012020.name: Automaton Spider
1012020.description: An automaton pieced together with Old World technology, tasked with replacing humans in performing the most basic forms of physical labor.\nIn combat, Automaton Spiders are highly unstable, capable of exploding when damaged.

1012021.name: Automaton Spider
1012021.description: An automaton pieced together with Old World technology, tasked with replacing humans in performing the most basic forms of physical labor.\nIn combat, Automaton Spiders are highly unstable, capable of exploding when damaged.

1012030.name: Automaton Beetle
1012030.description: An automaton pieced together with Old World technology. A signal light is placed on its legs, and the unit may have been used for mining or construction operations.\nIn combat, Automaton Beetles can create forcefields to shield themselves.

1012032.name: Amber King
1012032.description: Invincible. There's no other way to put it.

1012040.name: Auxiliary Robot Arm Unit
1012040.description: A mechanical device controlled by Svarog.\nWhen active on battlefield for certain turns, it will ruthlessly attack its enemies.

1012041.name: Auxiliary Robot Arm Unit
1012041.description: A mechanical device controlled by Svarog.\nWhen active on battlefield for certain turns, it will ruthlessly attack its enemies.

1012042.name: Auxiliary Robot Arm Unit
1012042.description: A mechanical device controlled by Svarog.\nAfter being active on the battlefield for a certain number of turns, this robot arm will ruthlessly attack its targets.

1013010.name: Automaton Grizzly
1013010.description: An automaton pieced together with Old World technology. It has been reinforced with durable armor, so it can charge forward and protect the Silvermane Guards.\nIn combat, Automaton Grizzlys will summon Automaton Spiders and unleash a powerful charged attack.

1013011.name: Automaton Grizzly (Bug)
1013011.description: A false projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is an automaton pieced together with Old World technology. It's been reinforced with durable armor to charge forward and protect the Silvermane Guards.\nIn combat, Automaton Grizzlies (Bug) will send out a signal to summon Automaton Spiders and Beatles, and at the same time unleash powerful charged attacks.

1013012.name: Automaton Grizzly (Complete)
1013012.description: A complete projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is an automaton pieced together with Old World technology. It's been reinforced with durable armor so that it could charge into battle and offer protection for the Silvermane Guards.\nIn combat, Automaton Grizzly (Complete) will send out a signal to summon Automaton Spiders, and at the same time unleash powerful charged attacks.

1013013.name: Automaton Grizzly (Complete)

1013020.name: Automaton Direwolf
1013020.description: An automaton pieced together with Old World technology. This rare type of humanoid automaton is equipped with a chainsaw on its right arm, presumably used for mining or construction operations.\nIn combat, Automaton Direwolfs will use their chainsaw to Bleed enemies, dealing DoT.

1014010.name: Svarog
1014010.description: An ancient relic from the Old World, that was originally used as an automated control unit by the Geomarrow Development Group. Unlike the vast majority of machines that lack intellect and can only act on command, Svarog is capable of much more complex thinking.\nIn battle, Svarog summons mechanical arms to grab and control his enemies, delivering devastating attacks.

1014011.name: Svarog (Complete)
1014011.description: A complete projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is an ancient relic from the Old World, that was originally used as an automated control unit by the Geomarrow Development Group. Unlike the vast majority of machines that lack intellect and can only act on command, Svarog is capable of much more complex thinking.\nIn battle, Svarog (Complete) can summon various machines as well as a robot arm unit to grab and control enemies while unleashing devastating strikes.

1022010.name: Everwinter Shadewalker
1022010.description: Shades that wander in the Fragmentum after the arrival of the Eternal Freeze. It mimics the form of the Silvermane Guards in a twisted manner. Fitted with the same uniformed armors as the Belobog warriors, its skull is however replaced by an icicle of faceless ice.\nEverwinter Shadewalkers will swing their ice ax and slow their enemies in battle.

1022020.name: Incineration Shadewalker
1022020.description: Shades that wander in the Fragmentum after the arrival of the Eternal Freeze. It mimics the form of the Silvermane Guards in a twisted manner. Fitted with the same uniformed armors as the Belobog warriors, its skull is however replaced by faceless embers.\nIncineration Shadewalkers will swing their fiery ax and burn their enemies in battle.

1023010.name: Searing Prowler
1023010.description: A machine unit prowling in the Fragmentum. Undoubtedly, this monstrosity is not a human creation, but one that was born out of the perversion of the Fragmentum.\nSearing Prowler's attacks will deal extra damage against enemies afflicted with Burn.

1023011.name: Searing Prowler (Bug)
1023011.description: A false projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is a machine unit prowling in the Fragmentum. Undoubtedly, this monstrosity is not a human creation, but one that was born out of the perversion of the Fragmentum.\nThe attacks of Searing Prowler (Bug) will deal extra damage against Burned enemies.

1023020.name: Frigid Prowler
1023020.description: A machine unit prowling in the Fragmentum. Undoubtedly, this monstrosity is not a human creation, but one that was born out of the perversion of the Fragmentum.\nFrigid Prowlers will attract Everwinter Shadewalkers and reduce its enemy's SPD and Ice RES.

1023021.name: Frigid Prowler (Bug)
1023021.description: A false projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is a machine unit prowling in the Fragmentum. Undoubtedly, this monstrosity is not a human creation, but one that was born out of the perversion of the Fragmentum.\nFrigid Prowler (Bug) will attract Everwinter Shadewalker and reduce its opponents' SPD and Ice RES.

1023022.name: IPC Team Leader Illusion
1023022.description: An Interastral Peace Corporation senior staff member with a minimal rank of project team leader. The mech they drive belongs to the IPC. If damaged, its repair fees have to be paid out-of-pocket. With a half-decent salary, they can at least afford to rent a one-bedroom apartment on one of the IPC's enterprise ships.

2002010.name: Cloud Knights Patroller
2002010.description: Member of the ground patrol division of the Xianzhou Luofu Cloud Knights. Wearing a light set of silver armor and with a Devastator Glaive in hand, they are in charge of maintaining order in every delve.

2002020.name: Flying Sword
2002020.description: Qi-controlled hovering attack unit, also named "Flying Sword." Closely connected to the wielder's psyche and can be used as an extension of its wielder's will.

2002021.name: Flying Sword
2002021.description: Qi-controlled hovering attack unit, also named "Flying Sword." Closely connected to the wielder's psyche and can be used as an extension of its wielder's will.

2002030.name: Wraith Warden
2002030.description: A somber warrior that accompanies the Judges of the Ten-Lords Commission to execute missions.\nAdorned with the black and white mask that symbolizes the netherworld envoy, they wield a guillotine blade, their strikes echoing the weighty and unyielding duty of the Ten-Lords Commission.

2002031.name: Wraith Warden
2002031.description: A somber warrior that accompanies the Judges of the Ten-Lords Commission to execute missions.\nAdorned with the black and white mask that symbolizes the netherworld envoy, they wield a guillotine blade, their strikes echoing the weighty and unyielding duty of the Ten-Lords Commission.

2002032.name: Wraith Warden
2002032.description: A somber warrior that accompanies the Judges of the Ten-Lords Commission to execute missions.\nAdorned with the black and white mask that symbolizes the netherworld envoy, they wield a guillotine blade, their strikes echoing the weighty and unyielding duty of the Ten-Lords Commission.

2004010.name: Stellaron Hunter: Kafka
2004010.description: One of the Stellaron Hunters. A beautiful assassin wearing an enigmatic smile, she excels in manipulation and various weaponry. It was by her design that the Astral Express was led here, all of which was simply part of a certain plan...

2004011.name: Stellaron Hunter: Kafka (Complete)
2004011.description: A complete projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is one of the Stellaron Hunters. A beautiful assassin wearing an enigmatic smile, she excels in manipulation and weaponry of various kinds. It was by her design that the Astral Express was led where it is now, all of which was simply part of a certain unknown plan...

2004012.name: Stellaron Hunter: Kafka (Complete)
2004012.description: A complete projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is one of the Stellaron Hunters. A beautiful assassin wearing an enigmatic smile, she excels in manipulation and weaponry of various kinds. It was by her design that the Astral Express was led where it is now, all of which was simply part of a certain unknown plan...

2004013.name: Stellaron Hunter: Kafka (Illusion)
2004013.description: One of the Stellaron Hunters. A beautiful assassin wearing an enigmatic smile, she excels in manipulation and various weaponry. It was by her design that the Astral Express was led here, all of which was simply part of a certain plan... This entity is a phantom borne from your memories.

2004014.name: Soulhook Sovereign
2004014.description: One of the Stellaron Hunters. A beautiful assassin wearing an enigmatic smile, she excels in manipulation and various weaponry. It was by her design that the Astral Express was led here, all of which was simply part of a certain plan...

2004020.name: Cloud Knight Lieutenant: Yanqing
2004020.description: General Jing Yuan's retainer. A gifted swordsman who hasn't even come of age.

2004021.name: Cloud Knight Lieutenant: Yanqing (Complete)
2004021.description: A complete projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is General Jing Yuan's retainer, a gifted swordsman who hasn't even come of age.

2004022.name: Cloud Knight Lieutenant: Yanqing (Complete)
2004022.description: A complete projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is General Jing Yuan's retainer, a gifted swordsman who hasn't even come of age.

2004023.name: Cloud Knight Lieutenant: Yanqing (Illusion)
2004023.description: General Jing Yuan's retainer. A gifted swordsman who hasn't even come of age. This entity is a phantom borne from your memories.

2004024.name: Cloud Knight Lieutenant: Yanqing
2004024.description: General Jing Yuan's retainer. A gifted swordsman who hasn't even come of age.

2004025.name: Cloud Knight Lieutenant: Yanqing
2004025.description: General Jing Yuan's retainer. A gifted swordsman who hasn't even come of age.

2004026.name: Cloud Knight Lieutenant: Yanqing (Corrupted)
2004026.description: General Jing Yuan's retainer. A gifted swordsman who hasn't even come of age.

2005010.name: Maddened Feixiao
2005010.description: The Merlin's Claw, who swallowed down the Crimson Moon to salvage the crisis and therefore descended into madness.\nPossessed by the monster within born of yesteryear's unending battles, Feixiao turned into a tireless avatar of war. As her friend and present enemy, you understand that the only "antidote"... is to keep fighting.

2011010.name: Entranced Ingenium: Obedient Dracolion
2011010.description: An ingenium casually made by craftsmasters of the Artisanship Commission. It was originally an inanimate alarm bell used for warnings, but now it has been given a short-lived "life" due to certain mutations.

2011020.name: Entranced Ingenium: Golden Cloud Toad
2011020.description: An ingenium casually made by craftsmasters of the Artisanship Commission. It was originally an inanimate burner used for purifying the air, but now it has been given a short-lived "life" due to certain mutations.

2012010.name: Entranced Ingenium: Illumination Dragonfish
2012010.description: An ingenium casually made by craftsmasters of the Artisanship Commission. It was originally an inanimate illuminator used for casting light upon darkness, but now it has been given a short-lived "life" due to certain mutations.

2013010.name: Aurumaton Gatekeeper
2013010.description: Garrison aurumaton created with ancient ingenium technology.\nCountless years ago, the aurumatons set sail with the Xianzhou to seek divine recipes of immortality, and were tasked to oversee humanity and to aid humankind during warfare. However, after countless rebellions, they were finally overpowered by the Xianzhou natives.\nNow, all aurumatons are strictly controlled with talismans, and are employed to guard important places.

2013011.name: Aurumaton Gatekeeper (Bug)
2013011.description: A false projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is the garrison aurumatons created with ancient ingenium technology.\nCountless years ago, the aurumatons set sail with the Xianzhou to seek divine recipes of immortality, and were tasked to oversee humanity and to aid humankind during warfare. However, after countless rebellions, they were finally overpowered by the Xianzhou natives.\nNow, all aurumatons are strictly controlled with talismans, and are employed to guard important places.

2013012.name: Aurumaton Gatekeeper
2013012.description: Garrison aurumaton created with ancient ingenium technology.\nCountless years ago, the aurumatons set sail with the Xianzhou to seek divine recipes of immortality, and were tasked with overseeing humanity and aiding humankind during warfare. However, after countless rebellions, they were finally overpowered by the Xianzhou natives.\nNow, all aurumatons are strictly controlled with talismans and are employed to guard important places.

2013020.name: Aurumaton Spectral Envoy
2013020.description: A law-enforcing aurumaton engraved with the Ten-Lords Martial Scriptures and taking orders from the Ten-Lords Commission.\nLiving beings are susceptible to the corporeal and mental existence of the self, but gold and metal will never be swayed and will unwaveringly follow the Ten-Lords' edicts.\nThese aurumaton law enforcers use their strength to subdue evils that have strayed from the natural order of life, and bring them to the Netherworld to meet their sentence. Its authority is sometimes even greater than that of a judge.

2013021.name: Aurumaton Spectral Envoy (Bug)
2013021.description: A false projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is a law-enforcing aurumaton engraved with the Ten-Lords Martial Scriptures and taking orders from the Ten-Lords Commission.\nLiving beings are susceptible to the corporeal and mental existence of the self, but gold and metal will never be swayed and will unwaveringly follow the Ten-Lords' edicts.\nThese aurumaton law enforcers use their strength to subdue evils that have strayed from the natural order of life, and bring them to the Netherworld to meet their sentence. Its authority is sometimes even greater than that of a judge.

2022010.name: Mara-Struck Soldier
2022010.description: Soldiers of the Xianzhou who somehow fell into madness. Their bodies continue to grow and mutate and have long lost their humanoid form. It is said that the long-lived Xianzhou natives would eventually be stricken with mara.

2022020.name: Disciples of Sanctus Medicus: Internal Alchemist
2022020.description: A member of the Disciples of Sanctus Medicus, the secret sect that hid within the Xianzhou Luofu. \nWith medicine, purify the heart. With elixir, transform one's body. They long to revive the ancient mysteries of Abundance, hoping to spur Xianzhou natives towards their next stage of evolution.

2022040.name: Abundance Sprite: Golden Hound
2022040.description: A gilded hunting hound that moves with grace and speed.\nWhen the Ambrosial Arbor still stood, the Xianzhou people bred many fantastic creatures with esoteric techniques. Golden Hounds were one of the war beasts that walked alongside the army.

2022050.name: Abundance Sprite: Wooden Lupus

It should be serving in the Charmony Festival, but it is now bound by Order and keeps performing scenes of the "Present." The present is a feast lasting through the night, desire for joy rippling in each cup, offering fine brews to the host who sets the banquet.

3004023.name: Thousand-Faced Skott
3004023.description: Skott, who gathered all the filming resources to become the greatest protagonist of all protagonists. With his consciousness and soul scattered by a Servant, he seeks revenge from the Trailblazer in a thousand different appearances.

3011010.name: Memory Zone Meme "Allseer"
3011010.description: An entity infused with a certain cognition, constructed from fragments of subconsciousness in the Memory Zone.\nObservation, retrospection, inspection... In the pursuit of preservation and existential understanding of the self, the memories of "seeing" and "looking" go hand-in-hand, eventually becoming an integral part of life itself.

3012010.name: Memory Zone Meme "Something In The Mirror"
3012010.description: An entity imbued with specific cognition, formed by the accumulation of subconscious fragments in the Memory Zone.\nLife forms use mirrors to understand the world and build their self-cognition. The shapeless memetic entity reflects in the mirror, leaving behind ever-shifting mirages.

3012020.name: Memory Zone Meme "Heartbreaker"
3012020.description: An entity imbued with specific cognition, formed by the accumulation of subconscious fragments in the Memory Zone.\nLife is parceled in impenetrable barriers, obstructing the intrusion of the alien. But beneath that ironclad shell, there is a region both nameless and fragile.

3012030.name: Sombrous Sepulcher
3012030.description: Shattered existences serve as symbols of ultimate closure. Across the ethereal expanse, spirits cast their gaze upon the mortal realm, their eyes reflecting the etchings of oblivion and separation.\nInnocent souls slumber within the Sombrous Sepulcher. Defeat the Tomb to awaken them.

3012040.description: An entity imbued with specific cognition, formed by the accumulation of subconscious fragments in the Memory Zone.\nThe boasting of bystanders, the clinging of the weak, the flattery of the servile... The endless vanity shifts into a memetic lifeform, seeking a host that covets both fame and fortune.

3013010.name: Memory Zone Meme "Shell of Faded Rage"
3013010.description: An entity imbued with specific cognition, formed by the accumulation of subconscious fragments in the Memory Zone.\nMemories of anguish burn like flames, scorching the heart. When the suffering fades away, the life born from resentment will rise from the ashes, accumulating boundless fury.

3025010.description: Dominicus, the wisher of the Harmonious Choir, is one of the many embodiments of Xipe the Harmony. Due to the interferences from the Order, his appearance is different from before. Materialized as the Hive Mind's response to wishes, the hymns he conducts can reshape the world and create new laws per the wishes, and all who made this wish will become the source of his power.

4012010.name: Furiae Warrior
4012010.description: A Titankin sculpted by "Strife." They are infused with Nikador's golden ichor. Their robust bodies are the shields of the army, and they use their stony corpus to cut off their foes, while their powerful limbs carry rations across the battlefield. They are also used as sparring partners by the soldiers of Kremnos.

4012020.name: Furiae Philosopher
4012020.description: A Titankin sculpted by "Strife." They are infused with Nikador's golden ichor. They contain plundered "rationality" within their vessels. The reason behind their creation is not truly toward the study of universal knowledge, but to delve deep into brutal martial tactics and the merciless laws of survival, further spreading madness masquerading as philosophy.

4012021.name: Furiae Philosopher

The reason behind their creation is not truly toward the study of universal knowledge, but to delve deep into brutal martial tactics and the merciless laws of survival, further spreading madness masquerading as philosophy.

4012030.name: Furiae Archer
4012030.description: A Titankin sculpted by "Strife." They are infused with Nikador's golden ichor. With faith as steadfast as flying arrows, they are the means to find prey for Kremnos' forces, hunting down beasts and foes across the wastes, and ensuring none survive within firing range.

4012031.name: Furiae Archer

4012040.name: Furiae Troupe
4012040.description: A Titankin sculpted by "Strife." They are infused with Nikador's golden ichor. They are singers under the Lance of Fury. In their lyrics come praises for soldiers and the mad king, using divine spells to call upon Nikador's blessings.

4012050.name: "Spirithief" Bartholos
4012050.description: The twin sprites roaming the wilds and alleys of Amphoreus, taking pleasure in stealing valuables and playing tricks on travelers. They often outpace Treasure Hunters at the last moment, leaving only a coin as a harmless joke.

4012060.name: Conquer or Be Conquered
4012060.description: The tip of its spear has drawn a boundless border.\nThe people and soldiers within the border are marked as conquered, or ones to be conquered.\nThe blood of the fearful will become honey for the divine body, and the souls of the defiant will walk into the palace of glory under the River of Souls.

4012090.description: Theos Synthetos's wandering monocular eye. It lacks imaging capability and primarily functions to assist the main eye in polarizing the weather.

4013010.name: Furiae Praetor
4013010.description: A Titankin sculpted by "Strife." They are infused with Nikador's golden ichor. They are mighty constructs capable of housing a Titan's soul. With their greatswords, they stand ready to repel the rush of the black tide or turn their blade in a countering onslaught in times of war.\nFuriae Praetor will sacrifice their weaker kin, exchanging atrocity for divine punishments from the Titan.

4014010.name: Savage God, Mad King, Incarnation of Strife
4014010.description: The Titan of Strife continues the mad war in their frenzy, becoming the unconquerable fear of the masses of Amphoreus.\nThey once were famed through glory, earning respect from gods and from the people of the land. And yet, the city that revered them was sundered, and the poems that praised their name were destroyed. Only their evil reputation lingers in this lightless era and end times, tainting the Throne of Worlds' brilliance.

4014020.name: The Giver, Master of Legions, Lance of Fury
4014020.description:
The undefeated. The sovereign of all battles. The king of Castrum Kremnos and of ruins,
Grand Artisan of the war chariot, the throne upon a mountain of corpses, and father of victory,
The tyrant of glories, the lightning that split the sea, the Guardian of Amphoreus,
The Titan of Strife, the Lance of Fury: Nikador.
A general that all the world should heed, the eternal sharp sword, the law of Strife and of ending Strife.
Praise Nikador, greatest of conquerors, greatest of guardians.

Praise Mydeimos, greatest of conquerors, greatest of guardians, the strongest of all.

4014030.name: Pollux, Netherwing Husk, Ferry of Souls
4014030.description: Netherwing, slumbering dormant in the River of Souls, has been reawakened by an alchemical summoning and morphed into a thing of rot and decay.\nIt once was the Death Titan, swimming upstream in the River of Souls' currents, leaving the realm of non-existence and stranded in the mortal world. Once, they followed the tides of the River of Souls to drown the living lands, branding all things in Amphoreus with a fated end. All the existences that will die or have died will feel a shudder in the depths of their souls with the dragon's return.

4014031.name: Pollux, Netherwing Husk, Ferry of Souls (Complete)
4014031.description: A complete projection produced by compromised codes. The referenced entity is Netherwing: Pollux, the slumbering dragon in the River of Souls, which has been reawakened by an alchemical summoning and morphed into a thing of rot and decay.\nIt once was the Death Titan, swimming upstream in the River of Souls' currents, leaving the realm of non-existence and stranded in the mortal world. Once, they followed the tides of the River of Souls to drown the living lands, branding all things in Amphoreus with a fated end. All the existences that will die or have died will feel a shudder in the depths of their souls with the dragon's return.

4014032.description: Netherwing, slumbering dormant in the River of Souls, has been reawakened by an alchemical summoning and morphed into a thing of rot and decay.\nIt once was the Death Titan, swimming upstream in the River of Souls' currents, leaving the realm of non-existence and stranded in the mortal world. Once, they followed the tides of the River of Souls to drown the living lands, branding all things in Amphoreus with a fated end. All the existences that will die or have died will feel a shudder in the depths of their souls with the dragon's return.

4014033.name: Castorice, Hand of Shadow
4014033.description: The broken body of "Death" that remains in the limbo of life and death, they woke once again to fight against fate.\nThe demigod could not bear to witness a friend walk toward an end more cruel than Death, and thus reached out their long arm to stop the friend. Even though withered bones and rotting flesh are all they have left, their power and determination are not to be underestimated.

4014035.name: Pollux, Netherwing Husk, Ferry of Souls (Corrupted)
4014035.description: Netherwing, slumbering dormant in the River of Souls, has been reawakened by an alchemical summoning and morphed into a thing of rot and decay.\nIt once was the Death Titan, swimming upstream in the River of Souls' currents, leaving the realm of non-existence and stranded in the mortal world. Once, they followed the tides of the River of Souls to drown the living lands, branding all things in Amphoreus with a fated end. All the existences that will die or have died will feel a shudder in the depths of their souls with the dragon's return.

4014036.name: Guide of Withering and Decay
4014036.description: Netherwing, slumbering dormant in the River of Souls, has been reawakened by an alchemical summoning and morphed into a thing of rot and decay.\nIt once was the Death Titan, swimming upstream in the River of Souls' currents, leaving the realm of non-existence and stranded in the mortal world. Once, they followed the tides of the River of Souls to drown the living lands, branding all things in Amphoreus with a fated end. All the existences that will die or have died will feel a shudder in the depths of their souls with the dragon's return.

4015010.name: Sublime, Radiant, Avatar of the Sky
4015010.description: The Sky Titan. Theos Synthetos. Conquered by and fused with humanity, they no longer govern Amphoreus' cycle of day and night, yet their aloof pride remains unchanged.\nIn their mind, the shattered world's mundane mortals are unsightly — compared to a world safeguarded by light, the mindless human masses seem more befitting of the black tide.

4015011.name: Sublime, Radiant, Avatar of the Sky
4015011.description: The Sky Titan. Theos Synthetos. Conquered by and fused with humanity, they no longer govern Amphoreus' cycle of day and night, yet their aloof pride remains unchanged.\nIn their mind, the shattered world's mundane mortals are unsightly — compared to a world safeguarded by light, the mindless human masses seem more befitting of the black tide.

4015020.name: Decimator, Karma of Daythunder, Eye of Twilight
4015020.description: The image of the conqueror who once ruled the skies with absolute might, now consumed by the black tide. The rights and wrongs of their past may be difficult to judge, but at this moment, all that remains is a formless blaze of karmic destruction, seething with murderous intent.

4015021.name: Hyacinthia, Eye of Twilight
4015021.description: This is what the demigod who mended the dawn with their smile looks like after they have been enveloped by the black tide. Although the brilliance of the Coreflame has been clouded, warmth still lingers —\nThe healer never wants to annihilate their old friend, instead vowing to disperse the gloomy clouds in the friend's heart.

4022010.name: Meteoric Eagle
4022010.description: In the ancient Era Creatura, Aquila, after forging the Dawn Device, collaborated with Kephale to bring forth the legendary beasts embodying the Titans. It is whispered that the Meteoric Eagle is a symbol of Aquila's celestial feathers that occasionally fall to the mortal realm.

4023010.name: Noontide Gryphon
4023010.description: In the ancient Era Creatura, Aquila, after forging the Dawn Device, collaborated with Kephale to bring forth the legendary beasts embodying the Titans. The Noontide Gryphon is said to represent Aquila after opening their eyes to bestow light upon the world.

4023020.name: Moonlit Pegasus
4023020.description: In the ancient Era Creatura, Aquila, after forging the Dawn Device, collaborated with Kephale to bring forth the legendary beasts embodying the Titans. The Moonlit Pegasus is believed to represent Aquila's eternal rival, Oronyx.

4032010.name: Tide-Eroded Blade
4032010.description: A creature warped by the black tide, driven solely by an insatiable thirst for bloodshed.\nIts razor-sharp blades can cleave through anything in its path, while its figure moves like a specter, spreading decay and corrosion to every corner of the world.

4032020.name: Long-Shattered Vessel
4032020.description: Each and every clone summoned by the Flame Reaver using the Calamity Power is a seed of ruin harboring the will of destruction within.

4032021.name: Long-Shattered Vessel
4032021.description: Each and every clone summoned by the Flame Reaver using the Calamity Power is a seed of ruin harboring the will of destruction within.

4032022.name: Long-Shattered Vessel
4032022.description: Each and every fragment reflected from endless calamities is a seed of ruin harboring the will of destruction within.

4032023.name: Demon King's Minions
4032023.description: The Black Cloak Demon King's devoted retainers. Inherited part of the Demon King's power and violent personality. There's evidence of their crimes on every planet.

4032024.name: Long-Shattered Vessel
4032024.description: Each and every clone summoned by the Flame Reaver using the Calamity Power is a seed of ruin harboring the will of destruction within.

4032025.name: Long-Shattered Vessel
4032025.description: Each and every fragment reflected from endless calamities is a seed of ruin harboring the will of destruction within.

4032026.name: Long-Shattered Vessel
4032026.description: Each and every clone summoned by the Flame Reaver using the Calamity Power is a seed of ruin harboring the will of destruction within.

4032030.name: Black Tide's Corroded Axe
4032030.description: A creature warped by the black tide, driven solely by an insatiable thirst for bloodshed.\nWielding a massive axe weighing a thousand pounds, its charged strike can shatter even the hardest stone. Any living being that stands in its way is doomed to be crushed and corroded.

4032040.name: Black Tide Council
4032040.description: A creature warped by the black tide, driven solely by an insatiable thirst for bloodshed.\nKnowledge that once could have served humanity has inverted into civilization's foe. Specializing in ambush and strategic maneuvers, they hover like ravenous vultures, craving to deliver fresh sacrifices to the black tide.

4032050.name: Black Tide's Decrepit Bow
4032050.description: A creature warped by the black tide, driven solely by an insatiable thirst for bloodshed.\nHolding a bow imbued with a curse, it can simultaneously attack targets in multiple directions while shooting. Any living being that enters its sight is doomed to face the inescapable aim of its arrows.

4033010.name: Black Tide's Corroded Daemon
4033010.description: A creature warped by the black tide, driven solely by an insatiable thirst for bloodshed.\nIts once-human form is now engulfed in filth, exuding a nauseating aura of corrosion. Wherever the Corroded Beast treads, all life is stripped away.

4033020.name: Black Tide's Champion
4033020.description: A creature warped by the black tide, driven solely by an insatiable thirst for bloodshed.\nIts dueling spirit, once fierce in life, has been twisted by the black tide. Wielding a massive greatsword as tall as its shoulders, it wanders aimlessly, seeking any target to destroy, offering yet more entropy to the chaos of the world.

4033030.name: Dark Sun Gryphon
4033030.description: Noontide Gryphon corroded by the black tide, driven solely by an insatiable thirst for bloodshed.\nEven after losing Aquila's blessings, the inexhaustible energy within the black tide has turned it into something even more horrifying.

4034010.name: Flame Reaver of the Deepest Dark
4034010.description: A nameless swordmaster who came with the black tide and is hunting down the Titans' Coreflame. None knows their true identity.\nTheir power is incredible, and their swordplay is nigh impeccable. Within their sword, madness and obsession entwine, once leading to the fall of the Grove of Epiphany and Aedes Elysiae.

4034011.description: A nameless swordmaster who came with the black tide and is hunting down the Titans' Coreflame. None knows their true identity.\nTheir power is incredible, and their swordplay is nigh impeccable. Within their sword, madness and obsession entwine, once leading to the fall of the Grove of Epiphany and Aedes Elysiae.

4034012.name: "Black Cloak Demon King"
4034012.description: A horrifying Demon King that resides in the depths of the cosmos, with the power to stomp on the galaxy and punch through black holes. Millions of planets have been shrouded under his black cloak, and the entire cosmos pleads for a hero who can overthrow the Demon King's reign.

4034013.name: Flame Reaver of Doomsday Led Astray
4034013.description: A nameless swordmaster who came with the black tide and is hunting down the Titans' Coreflame. None knows their true identity.\nTheir power is incredible, and their swordplay is nigh impeccable. Within their swords, madness and obsession entwine, once leading to the fall of the Grove of Epiphany and Aedes Elysiae.

4034014.name: Flame Reaver of the Deepest Dark
4034014.description: A nameless swordmaster who came with the black tide and is hunting down the Titans' Coreflame. None knows their true identity.\nTheir power is incredible, and their swordplay is nigh impeccable. Within their swords, madness and obsession entwine, once leading to the fall of the Grove of Epiphany and Aedes Elysiae.

4034015.name: Dawn-Denied Khaslana
4034015.description: A nameless swordsman, borne by the black tide to hunt Coreflames, wears a mask carved with the stoic visage of a deliverer... Yet his form crumbles like dying kindling.\n From the flames echoes hollowness: All is futility.

4034017.name: Flame Reaver of the Deepest Dark
4034017.description: A nameless swordmaster who came with the black tide and is hunting down the Titans' Coreflame. None knows their true identity.\nTheir power is incredible, and their swordplay is nigh impeccable. Within their swords, madness and obsession entwine, once leading to the fall of the Grove of Epiphany and Aedes Elysiae.

4034018.description: A nameless swordsman, borne by the black tide to hunt Coreflames, wears a mask carved with the stoic visage of a deliverer... Yet his form crumbles like dying kindling.\n From the flames echoes hollowness: All is futility.

4034019.name: Flame Reaver of the Deepest Dark (Corrupted)
4034019.description: A nameless swordmaster who came with the black tide and is hunting down the Titans' Coreflame. None knows their true identity.\nTheir power is incredible, and their swordplay is nigh impeccable. Within their swords, madness and obsession entwine, once leading to the fall of the Grove of Epiphany and Aedes Elysiae.

4043010.name: Herta #ErrorModel
4043010.description: A Herta puppet corrupted by a Memory Zone Meme. As it is a perfect model, it still looks exquisite and practical despite the errors consuming its parameters.

4044010.name: First Genius, Entelechy, Zandar
4044010.description: The Theoros who had silently observed hundreds of millions of cycles in the name of Lycurgus, and inherited the will of Genius Society member #1, Zandar One Kuwabara. With the authority of the very first Genius, he wields power beyond that of legends and gods, in an attempt to lead a long-running experiment toward the fate of Destruction.

4044011.name: First Genius, Entelechy, Zandar
4044011.description: The Theoros who had silently observed hundreds of millions of cycles in the name of Lycurgus, and inherited the will of Genius Society member #1, Zandar One Kuwabara. With the authority of the very first Genius, he wields power beyond that of legends and gods, in an attempt to lead a long-running experiment toward the fate of Destruction.

4052010.name: Servant of Tides
4052010.description:
Daughters of the sea, their souls and flesh corroded by the sins of "Destruction," now dance and chant for the coming Dark Sun as hollow, twisted husks.
The remnant black tide flows from past ages into this world's tides—
Loyal and fair waves, bathing in the mud that overflows from your master's cup... your pristine skirts stained with madness—
You drift directionless between surges of life and death, finding no solace, no moment's peace.

4052012.name: Servant of Tides
4052012.description:
Daughters of the sea, their souls and flesh corroded by the sins of "Destruction," now dance and chant for the coming Dark Sun as hollow, twisted husks.
The remnant black tide flows from past ages into this world's tides—
Loyal and fair waves, bathing in the mud that overflows from your master's cup... your pristine skirts stained with madness—
You drift directionless between surges of life and death, finding no solace, no moment's peace.

4053010.name: Lady of Crashing Waves
4053010.description:
Daughters of the sea, their souls and flesh corroded by the sins of "Destruction," now dance and chant for the coming Dark Sun as hollow, twisted husks.
The remnant black tide flows from past ages into this world's tides—
Enchanting waves, you drank calamity for your sovereign, and your visage is adorned with wine-stained petals and shattered pearls—
You lie drunken in the frenzied abattoir, and in this grave of blood and honeyed ruin, you sing your elegy into the void.

4053012.name: Lady of Crashing Waves
4053012.description:
Daughters of the sea, their souls and flesh corroded by the sins of "Destruction," now dance and chant for the coming Dark Sun as hollow, twisted husks.
The remnant black tide flows from past ages into this world's tides—
Enchanting waves, you drank calamity for your sovereign, and your visage is adorned with wine-stained petals and shattered pearls—
You lie drunken in the frenzied abattoir, and in this grave of blood and honeyed ruin, you sing your elegy into the void.

4062010.name: Ichor Memosprite: Pheasant
4062010.description: A distorted monster formed from the Garden of Recollection's memetic lifeform by the Destruction using golden ichor. It has begun to take the shape of a bird.\nIt is both raucous and always moves in cohesive groups, showing that even with humanity evaporated, its instinct of following the Destruction manifests in this manner.

4062020.name: Ichor Memosprite: Canine
4062020.description: A distorted monster formed from the Garden of Recollection's memetic lifeform by the Destruction using golden ichor. It has begun to take the shape of a dog.\nIt is aggressive, showing that even with humanity evaporated, its instinct of following the Destruction manifests in this manner.

4063010.name: Ichor Memosprite: Winged Serpent
4063010.description: A distorted monster formed from the Garden of Recollection's memetic lifeform by the Destruction using golden ichor. It is in the rudimentary form of a flying snake, enough to intimidate its assailants.\nIts twisted rationality went completely mad in the black tide, and its intense self-protecting impulse imperceptibly took on a fantastical flavor.

4064010.name: Ichor Memosprite: Judge of Oblivion
4064010.description: A trace of lingering madness extracted and refined by Evernight from the countless corpses of ichor memosprites, then synthesized into more twisted and grotesque monsters.\nIt shall follow the creator's directive, determining what should be remembered and what should be forgotten, devouring redundant memories that serve no purpose and leaving them muted in the flow of time.\n"If a new life is to be born, its seed has to be dead."

8001010.name: Flamespawn
8001010.description: Crystallized elements with only the simplest intelligence. It drifts in the Fragmentum in the form of a bird emitting intense heat, burning everything in its path.

8001020.name: Frostspawn
8001020.description: Crystallized elements with only the simplest intelligence. It drifts in the Fragmentum in the form of a bird releasing eerily low temperatures, freezing everything around it.

8001030.name: Mask of No Thought
8001030.description: Victims of Fragmentum corrosion pieced together into one bizarre creature, their numb faces forming a sphere without thought or emotion. Any part that was once human has since vanished.

8001040.name: Thunderspawn
8001040.description: Crystallized elements with only the simplest intelligence. It drifts in the Fragmentum in the form of a bird brimming with electricity, releasing thunderclaps in all directions.

8001050.name: Windspawn
8001050.description: Crystallized elements with only the simplest intelligence. It drifts in the Fragmentum in the form of a bird engulfed in twisting winds, raging on like a tornado.

8002010.name: Imaginary Weaver
8002010.description: Strange beings that do not belong to this world. Passing through countless barriers, they arrive from the other side of the vast, dark, starry sky. Their bodies are like diseased branches breaching into reality, using Imaginary power to twist reality at will.

8002040.name: Warp Trotter
8002040.description: An interdimensional creature lost in the stars. Docile in nature. Sweet in taste. Inedible. Spends most of its life feeding and fleeing. Travelers who encounter these creatures see them as good omens.

8002050.name: Sequence Trotter
8002050.description: An interdimensional creature lost in the stars. Docile in nature. Sweet in taste. Inedible. Spends most of its life feeding and fleeing. Travelers who encounter these creatures see them as good omens.

8002109.name: Sequence Trotter (Giant)
8002109.description: An interdimensional creature lost in the stars. Docile in nature. Sweet in taste. Inedible. Spends most of its life feeding and fleeing. Travelers who encounter these creatures see them as good omens.

8003010.name: Ice Out of Space
8003010.description: A strange being that does not belong to this world. Nurtured in the Fragmentum brought by the Stellaron, it feeds upon this world's root structures to obtain energy. Its armor reflects the gloomy and profound starry sky.\nIn combat, the Ice Out of Space will freeze targets it touches.

8003011.name: Ice Out of Space (Bug)
8003011.description: A false projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is an alien life form that was born out of the Fragmentum brought by a Stellaron and feeds on this world's energy. Its armor reflects the gloomy and profound starry sky.\nIn combat, the Ice Out of Space (Bug) will freeze targets it touches and delay their actions.

8003012.name: Ice Out of Space
8003012.description: A strange being that does not belong to this world. Nurtured in the Fragmentum brought by the Stellaron, it feeds upon this world's root structures to obtain energy. Its armor reflects the gloomy and profound starry sky.\nIn combat, the Ice Out of Space will freeze targets it touches.

8003020.name: Blaze Out of Space
8003020.description: A strange being that does not belong to this world. Nurtured in the Fragmentum created by the Stellaron, it parasitize upon this world's root structures to obtain energy. Its armor burns with the blazing flames in the core of stars.\nIn combat, the Blaze Out of Space will incinerate anything it touches.

8003021.name: Blaze Out of Space (Bug)
8003021.description: A false projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is an alien life form that was born out of the Fragmentum brought by a Stellaron and feeds on this world's energy. Its armor carries the flames taken from the core of a star.\nIn combat, the Blaze Out of Space (Bug) will incinerate anything it touches.

8003022.name: Blaze Out of Space
8003022.description: Born of the Fragmentum and created by the Stellaron, this alien life form feeds on this world's energy. The blazing fires from the core of a star burn on its armor.\nIn combat, the Blaze Out of Space will incinerate anything it touches.

8003030.name: Guardian Shadow
8003030.description: A shadow manifested by the power of a Stellaron, carrying out the Fragmentum's unceasing will to expand.\nA living being of energy born from the projection of the desires of sentient lifeforms into the Fragmentum, akin to a pearl created from a single grain of sand. This energy wanders around aimlessly, acting only when executing the will of its master.

8003031.name: Guardian Shadow (Bug)
8003031.description: A false projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is a shadow manifested by the power of Stellaron, carrying out the Fragmentum's unceasing will to expand.\nA physical manifestation of the desires of intelligent life in the Fragmentum, like a pearl created from a single grain of sand. This force wanders around aimlessly, acting only when executing the will of its master.

8003040.name: Decaying Shadow
8003040.description: A shadow manifested by the power of a Stellaron, carrying out the Fragmentum's unceasing will to expand.\nA living being of energy born from the projection of the desires of sentient lifeforms into the Fragmentum, akin to a pearl created from a single grain of sand. However, the desire that drove it has long since been twisted and distorted.

8003041.name: Decaying Shadow (Bug)
8003041.description: A false projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is a shadow manifested by the power of Stellaron, carrying out the Fragmentum's unceasing will to expand.\nA physical embodiment of the desires of intelligent life in the Fragmentum, like a pearl created from a single grain of sand. However, its purpose has long since been twisted and distorted.

8003042.name: Decaying Shadow
8003042.description: A shadow manifested by the power of Stellaron, carrying out the Fragmentum's unceasing will to expand.\nA physical embodiment of the desires of intelligent life in the Fragmentum, like a pearl created from a single grain of sand. However, its purpose has long been twisted and distorted.

8003050.name: Stormbringer
8003050.description: Monsters that have experienced corrosion as the Fragmentum expanded. They now have a more nimble way of fighting after the source of their power mutated.\nStormbringers utilize the power of the wind to aid them in battle, enabling them to fire arrows more rapidly.

8003051.name: Stormbringer (Bug)
8003051.description: A false projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is a monster that underwent corrosion in the expanse of the Fragmentum. It has developed a more agile fighting style ever since its original form became distorted.\nThe Stormbringer utilizes the power of the wind to its advantage in battle, enabling it to fire arrows more rapidly. It can also summon Windspawn to aid in combat.

8003052.name: Stormbringer
8003052.description: Monsters that have experienced corrosion as the Fragmentum expanded. They now have a more nimble way of fighting after the source of their power mutated.\nStormbringers utilize the power of the wind to aid them in battle, enabling them to fire arrows more rapidly.

8011010.name: Baryon
8011010.description: In order to prevent antiparticles from dissipating and annihilating normal matter, the Antimatter Legion created two types of miniature ion traps for transportation, collectively referred to as Baryons and Antibaryons.\nBaryons have basic intelligence, and can clear the path according to the commands and summons of Voidrangers on the battlefield.

8011020.name: Antibaryon
8011020.description: In order to prevent antiparticles from dissipating and annihilating normal matter, the Antimatter Legion created two types of miniature ion traps for transportation, collectively referred to as Baryons and Antibaryons.\nAntibaryons have basic intelligence, and can clear the path according to the commands and summons of Voidrangers on the battlefield.

8012010.name: Voidranger: Reaver
8012010.description: Warriors yet to perish were recast in the Warforge and gained Destruction's power. Antimatter completes their bodies and negative particles reverberate throughout their forms.\nViolently aggressive, they embody the will of Destruction and are basic combat units of the Antimatter Legion, acting only according to their destructive instincts.

8012020.name: Voidranger: Distorter
8012020.description: A Voidranger that has successfully survived particle annihilation, the positive and negative particles in its body have temporarily achieved a strange balance, granting them more power than ordinary reavers.\nBasic combat units of the Antimatter Legion. They possess some intelligence and are able to control reavers within a small surrounding area.

8012021.name: Voidranger: Distorter
8012021.description: A Voidranger that has successfully survived particle annihilation, the positive and negative particles in its body have temporarily achieved a strange balance, granting them more power than ordinary reavers.\nBasic combat units of the Antimatter Legion. They possess some intelligence and are able to control reavers within a small surrounding area.

8012030.name: Voidranger: Eliminator
8012030.description: Bodies that continued to be corroded by the Fragmentum after death. While their vital signs have changed, they continue to carry out their orders to eliminate.\nVoidranger: Eliminators will mark enemies they hit, causing them to take extra damage when attacked.

8012140.name: Disaster's Right Hand
8012140.description: Only the echoes of pain remain on the devastated earth — the march of the end times.\nDisaster's Right Hand is adept at drawing upon Imaginary power to create large-scale attacks.

8012142.name: Dawn's Left Hand
8012142.description: At the last dawn before the end, even the bright and clear morning sun will tremble and cower away.\nDawn's Left Hand is adept at drawing upon Quantum power to launch attacks at single targets.

8012200.description: A phantom flower that blooms without roots and forms out of thin air. Phantylia used the Ambrosial Arbor as her host to forge a physical body and to touch upon Abundance's authority.

8013010.name: Voidranger: Trampler
8013010.description: A product of the Antimatter Legion utilizing the Warforge to recast and fuse remnants of fallen warriors and Leviathans.\nThough relatively rare, they possess both the intelligence of a warrior and the power and mobility of a Leviathan. Its screech can summon a large number of Voidrangers.

8013011.description: A false projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is a product of the Antimatter Legion utilizing the Warforge to recast and fuse remnants of fallen warriors and Leviathans.\nThough relatively rare, they possess both the intelligence of a warrior and the power and mobility of a Leviathan. Its screech can summon many Voidrangers.

8013141.name: Antimatter Engine
8013141.description: The ultimate embodiment of power. The form of the energy that accumulates behind it remains unknown.\nThe Antimatter Engine will grant energy to other enemies and enhance their abilities.

8015010.name: Doomsday Beast
8015010.description: Using fragments of the Dusk Leviathan as the foundation, and the weeping bones of thousands of the dead in the Warforge as the agent, the Antimatter Legion cast the Doomsday Beast. The resentful spirits' senseless obsession turns into a tangible hand, and the shadow of the old disaster conceals the heavens. The Doomsday Beast detains the will of all beings that are not at ease and have yet to die. Anger, mourning, or delusional joy — all is revealed, and all evil eagerly throb. The Doomsday Beast's core is a dark matter engine.

8015020.name: Phantylia the Undying
8015020.description: The body born out of the Ambrosial Arbor by Phantylia, Lord Ravager of the Antimatter Legion.\nThis flesh possesses the powers of both Destruction and Abundance, a form that embodies the cycle of death and rebirth. It is also the first "fruit" borne from the rejuvenated Ambrosial Arbor.

8022030.name: Gnaw Sting
8022030.description: A subspecies of Stings that underwent mutations during reproduction, adept at using quantum toxins in their mandibles to corrode away the bodies of their prey.

8024010.name: Swarm: True Sting (Complete)
8024010.description: A complete projection produced by compromised codes. The referent entity is a mature True Sting. Sir Duroy, a member of the Intelligentsia Guild, explored the starry seas and authored the thirty-volume of the Chronicles of Interdimensional Insects. The book provides detailed records of over a dozen confirmed species of lepisma and countless subspecies spanning across the stars.

8025010.name: Starcrusher Swarm King: Skaracabaz (Synthetic)
8025010.description: The replica of the Emanator of Propagation cultivated by Ruan Mei, briefly manifesting in the world in an incomplete form. Its original form is a giant lepisma that inherited the mandibles of the Imperator Insectorum. It can collect in its mouthparts the death ray that fragmented celestial bodies, and make shattered stars incubators for procreating offspring. It was once one of the nightmares across multiple worlds during the Swarm Disaster.

8032010.description: An Interastral Peace Corporation grunt worker whose job mainly deals with shady "business oversights." With a meager salary, the only lodging they can afford is a shared room on one of the IPC's enterprise ships.

8033010.description: An Interastral Peace Corporation senior staff member with a minimal rank of project team leader. The mech they drive belongs to the IPC. 100206401.name: IPC Team Leader Illusion
100206401.description: An Interastral Peace Corporation senior staff member with a minimal rank of project team leader. The mech they drive belongs to the IPC. If damaged, its repair fees have to be paid out-of-pocket. With a half-decent salary, they can at least afford to rent a one-bedroom apartment on one of the IPC's enterprise ships.

100301101.description: A false projection produced by compromised codes. 101401001.name: Svarog
101401001.description: An ancient relic from the Old World, that was originally used as an automated control unit by the Geomarrow Development Group. 102201001.description: Shades that wander in the Fragmentum after the arrival of the Eternal Freeze. It mimics the form of the Silvermane Guards in a twisted manner. Fitted with the same uniformed armors as the Belobog warriors, its skull is however replaced by an icicle of faceless ice.\nEverwinter Shadewalkers will swing their ice ax and slow their enemies in battle.

102301001.name: Searing Prowler
102301001.description: A machine unit prowling in the Fragmentum. Undoubtedly, this monstrosity is not a human creation, but one that was born out of the perversion of the Fragmentum.\nSearing Prowler's attacks will deal extra damage against enemies afflicted with Burn.

102302201.name: IPC Team Leader Illusion
102302201.description: An Interastral Peace Corporation senior staff member with a minimal rank of project team leader. The mech they drive belongs to the IPC. If damaged, its repair fees have to be paid out-of-pocket. With a half-decent salary, they can at least afford to rent a one-bedroom apartment on one of the IPC's enterprise ships.

200201001.name: Distortion
200201001.description: "Memory" is similar to "photographs." Even though it appears to record "reality," it actually invades, alienates, and alters "reality." Perhaps removing the "distortion" will make it reliable, or perhaps not.

200201002.name: Cloud Knights Patroller
200201002.description: Member of the ground patrol division of the Xianzhou Luofu Cloud Knights. Wearing a light set of silver armor and with a Devastator Glaive in hand, they are in charge of maintaining order in every delve.

200203001.name: Wraith Warden
200203001.description: A somber warrior that accompanies the Judges of the Ten-Lords Commission to execute missions.\nAdorned with the black and white mask that symbolizes the netherworld envoy, they wield a guillotine blade, their strikes echoing the weighty and unyielding duty of the Ten-Lords Commission.

201301002.name: Aurumaton Gatekeeper
201301002.description: Garrison aurumaton created with ancient ingenium technology.\nCountless years ago, the aurumatons set sail with the Xianzhou to seek divine recipes of immortality, and were tasked to oversee humanity and to aid humankind during warfare. However, after countless rebellions, they were finally overpowered by the Xianzhou natives.\nNow, all aurumatons are strictly controlled with talismans, and are employed to guard important places.

201302001.name: Aurumaton Spectral Envoy
201302001.description: A law-enforcing aurumaton engraved with the Ten-Lords Martial Scriptures and taking orders from the Ten-Lords Commission.\nLiving beings are susceptible to the corporeal and mental existence of the self, but gold and metal will never be swayed and will unwaveringly follow the Ten-Lords' edicts.\nThese aurumaton law enforcers use their strength to subdue evils that have strayed from the natural order of life, and bring them to the Netherworld to meet their sentence. Its authority is sometimes even greater than that of a judge.

202204001.description: "Memory" is similar to "photographs." Even though it appears to record "reality," it actually invades, alienates, and alters "reality." Perhaps removing the "distortion" will make it reliable, or perhaps not.

202301001.name: Disciples of Sanctus Medicus: Shape Shifter
202301001.description: A cultivator who longs to revive the ancient mysteries of Abundance, and to guide the Xianzhou natives back on the liberating path of immortality.\nNow, their wish has been fulfilled. 202302001.name: Abundance Sprite: Malefic Ape
202302001.description: An ape as tall as mountainous boulders with terrifying might.\nWhen the Ambrosial Arbor still stood, the Xianzhou people bred many fantastic creatures with their esoteric techniques. Malefic Apes were one of the war beasts that walked alongside the army.

202302002.name: Phantylia
202302002.description: The form craved by the members of Disciples of Sanctus Medicus, a secret organization that worships Abundance. A true appearance that cast off the burdens of humanity and has been reforged using the way of immortality.\nIn ancient times, those who sought immortality received wisdom from the Ambrosial Arbor and called themselves Celestials. They lived without restraints and molded the flesh of themselves and others at will. They have long forgotten their original appearances after countless metamorphoses.

They lived without restraints and molded the flesh of themselves and others at will. They have long forgotten their original appearances after countless metamorphoses.

300205003.name: Lordly Trashcan
300205003.description: A peculiar entity born within the realm of fiction, its story documented in the nameless chronicles: A lone and valiant trashcan bearing the mission of the Garbage King to seek formidable warriors to eliminate all waste that threatens the world.

300205004.name: Head Judge
300205004.description: The inaugural winner of the Rumbas culinary competition, his insurmountable culinary skills had once towered above all the trashcans of the universe. There were <unbreak>666</unbreak> peers who lost their confidence and wallowed in apathy after tasting his trash works. To prevent such a tragedy from happening again, the nameless king of chefs took off his apron and left the culinary battlefield, and made it his duty to teach his skills to others instead.

300205201.name: Unit<unbreak>-01</unbreak>
300205201.description: A popular streamer imitating the Stellaron Hunter. The costume details are done very well, and at a glance, it surprisingly has a touch of SAM's style.

The future is an eternal ballad, a vision of happiness strung together, calling to the composing sovereign with the melody of a harp.

300305001.name: "Present Inebriated in Revelry"
300305001.description: A waiter responsible for entertaining the guests in the Sweet Dreams Troupe. It should be serving in the Charmony Festival, but it is now bound by Order and keeps performing scenes of the "Present." The present is a feast lasting through the night, desire for joy rippling in each cup, offering fine brews to the host who sets the banquet.

300401001.description: The actors of the Sweet Dreams Troupe have accepted the grace of the Order and become puppets that declare the law. They dance under the supreme commandments, beginning a show that will welcome the coming of paradise.

301201001.name: Memory Zone Meme "Something In The Mirror"
301201001.description: An entity imbued with specific cognition, formed by the accumulation of subconscious fragments in the Memory Zone.\nLife forms use mirrors to understand the world and build their self-cognition. The shapeless memetic entity reflects in the mirror, leaving behind ever-shifting mirages.

301202001.name: Memory Zone Meme "Heartbreaker"

But beneath that ironclad shell, there is a region both nameless and fragile.

302501001.name: "Embryo of Philosophy" Sunday
302501001.description: Using the Harmonious Choir as a foundation, the power of Order and Harmony intertwine to form the shell of an egg, within which the newborn god slumbers. The metaphysical embryo mumbles the olden dreams of childhood as the fetal movement of Paths throbs in the long night, futilely resisting the rising dawn.

302501301.name: Cacophonic Conductor
302501301.description: Dominicus, the wisher of the Harmonious Choir, is one of the many embodiments of Xipe the Harmony. Due to the interferences from the Order, his appearance is different from before. Materialized as the Hive Mind's response to wishes, the hymns he conducts can reshape the world and create new laws per the wishes, and all who made this wish will become the source of his power.

Due to the interferences from the Order, his appearance is different from before. Materialized as the Hive Mind's response to wishes, the hymns he conducts can reshape the world and create new laws per the wishes, and all who made this wish will become the source of his power.

401201004.name: Furiae Warrior
401201004.description: A Titankin sculpted by "Strife." They are infused with Nikador's golden ichor. Their robust bodies are the shields of the army, and they use their stony corpus to cut off their foes, while their powerful limbs carry rations across the battlefield. They are also used as sparring partners by the soldiers of Kremnos.

401202001.name: Furiae Philosopher
401202001.description: A Titankin sculpted by "Strife." They are infused with Nikador's golden ichor. They contain plundered "rationality" within their vessels. The reason behind their creation is not truly toward the study of universal knowledge, but to delve deep into brutal martial tactics and the merciless laws of survival, further spreading madness masquerading as philosophy.

401203001.name: Furiae Archer
401203001.description: A Titankin sculpted by "Strife." They are infused with Nikador's golden ichor. With faith as steadfast as flying arrows, they are the means to find prey for Kremnos' forces, hunting down beasts and foes across the wastes, and ensuring none survive within firing range.

401204001.description: A Titankin sculpted by "Strife." They are infused with Nikador's golden ichor. They are singers under the Lance of Fury. In their lyrics come praises for soldiers and the mad king, using divine spells to call upon Nikador's blessings.

401205001.name: "Spirithief" Bartholos
401205001.description: The twin sprites roaming the wilds and alleys of Amphoreus, taking pleasure in stealing valuables and playing tricks on travelers. They often outpace Treasure Hunters at the last moment, leaving only a coin as a harmless joke.

401206001.name: Conquer or Be Conquered
401206001.description: The tip of its spear has drawn a boundless border.\nThe people and soldiers within the border are marked as conquered, or ones to be conquered.\nThe blood of the fearful will become honey for the divine body, and the souls of the defiant will walk into the palace of glory under the River of Souls.

401207601.name: The Long Arms of Sorrow
401207601.description: All who wish to futilely escape the end must face the underworld's pursuit.

401301001.name: Furiae Praetor
401301001.description: A Titankin sculpted by "Strife." They are infused with Nikador's golden ichor. They are mighty constructs capable of housing a Titan's soul. With their greatswords, they stand ready to repel the rush of the black tide or turn their blade in a countering onslaught in times of war.\nFuriae Praetor will sacrifice their weaker kin, exchanging atrocity for divine punishments from the Titan.

401401001.name: Savage God, Mad King, Incarnation of Strife
401401001.description: The Titan of Strife continues the mad war in their frenzy, becoming the unconquerable fear of the masses of Amphoreus.\nThey once were famed through glory, earning respect from gods and from the people of the land. And yet, the city that revered them was sundered, and the poems that praised their name were destroyed. Only their evil reputation lingers in this lightless era and end times, tainting the Throne of Worlds' brilliance.

401402001.name: The Giver, Master of Legions, Lance of Fury
401402001.description:
The undefeated. The sovereign of all battles. The king of Castrum Kremnos and of ruins,
Grand Artisan of the war chariot, the throne upon a mountain of corpses, and father of victory,
The tyrant of glories, the lightning that split the sea, the Guardian of Amphoreus,
The Titan of Strife, the Lance of Fury: Nikador.
A general that all the world should heed, the eternal sharp sword, the law of Strife and of ending Strife.
Praise Nikador, greatest of conquerors, greatest of guardians.

401403601.name: Guide of Withering and Decay
401403601.description: Netherwing, slumbering dormant in the River of Souls, has been reawakened by an alchemical summoning and morphed into a thing of rot and decay.\nIt once was the Death Titan, swimming upstream in the River of Souls' currents, leaving the realm of non-existence and stranded in the mortal world. Once, they followed the tides of the River of Souls to drown the living lands, branding all things in Amphoreus with a fated end. All the existences that will die or have died will feel a shudder in the depths of their souls with the dragon's return.

401501001.name: Sublime, Radiant, Avatar of the Sky
401501001.description: The Sky Titan. Theos Synthetos. Conquered by and fused with humanity, they no longer govern Amphoreus' cycle of day and night, yet their aloof pride remains unchanged.\nIn their mind, the shattered world's mundane mortals are unsightly — compared to a world safeguarded by light, the mindless human masses seem more befitting of the black tide.

401502001.name: Decimator, Karma of Daythunder, Eye of Twilight
401502001.description: The image of the conqueror who once ruled the skies with absolute might, now consumed by the black tide. The rights and wrongs of their past may be difficult to judge, but at this moment, all that remains is a formless blaze of karmic destruction, seething with murderous intent.

402201001.name: Meteoric Eagle
402201001.description: In the ancient Era Creatura, Aquila, after forging the Dawn Device, collaborated with Kephale to bring forth the legendary beasts embodying the Titans. It is whispered that the Meteoric Eagle is a symbol of Aquila's celestial feathers that occasionally fall to the mortal realm.

402301001.name: Noontide Gryphon
402301001.description: In the ancient Era Creatura, Aquila, after forging the Dawn Device, collaborated with Kephale to bring forth the legendary beasts embodying the Titans. The Noontide Gryphon is said to represent Aquila after opening their eyes to bestow light upon the world.

403201002.name: Tide-Eroded Blade
